On client:

    Install VS Code.

    Install "Remote Development" extension pack for VS Code.

    Install an OpenSSH compatible SSH client if one is not already present. See & download from: https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/remote/troubleshooting#_installing-a-supported-ssh-client

On server:

    Configure key based authentication on the host. Follow these steps: https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/remote/troubleshooting#_configuring-key-based-authentication
        To create a public SSH key on the local machine and copy its contents to the remote host.

On client:

    If you have previously connected to another host with the same domain name, first remove it from the .ssh/known_hosts in the client device under the user's folder.
    
On VS Code: 

    Press (F1) and run this command: ">Remote-SSH: Connect Current Window to Host...".
    
    Go to extension tab and install already installed extensions on host too.
    
    Open remote settings and modify it if required, for example activate format on save.
    
